---
---

<section class="section" id="problem">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6">

    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-primary-light mb-4">The Problem</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight">
        You already have WPML.<br />
        <span class="text-slate-400 font-medium">Now what?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 max-w-[480px] mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        WPML gives you the structure. But translating the content is still on you — and every option comes with a catch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">

      <!-- Pain 1 -->
      <div class="problem-card group">
        <div class="icon-wrap mb-5">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M3 10h14M10 3v14" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="7.5" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="1.4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">
          Per-word pricing adds up fast
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          WPML's own translation services charge around <strong class="text-slate-400">€0.07 per word</strong>. A 10,000-word site costs €700 — and that's before any updates.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-border">
          <span class="text-xs text-slate-600">WPML Translation Services: ~€0.07/word</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pain 2 -->
      <div class="problem-card group">
        <div class="icon-wrap mb-5">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="7.5" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.4"/>
            <path d="M10 6v4l2.5 2.5" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">
          Manual translation doesn't scale
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Every time you update a page, a product description or a blog post — someone has to translate it again. That's not a workflow, that's a bottleneck.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-border">
          <span class="text-xs text-slate-600">Typical agency rate: €0.10–0.20/word</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pain 3 -->
      <div class="problem-card group">
        <div class="icon-wrap mb-5">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <rect x="3" y="6" width="14" height="10" rx="2" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="1.4"/>
            <path d="M7 6V5a3 3 0 016 0v1" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle cx="10" cy="11" r="1.5" fill="#6366f1" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-semibold text-[15px] mb-2">
          Generic AI tools have no control
        </h3>
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Other AI plugins support one provider, offer no glossary, no prompt control, no cost transparency — and still require you to manually copy results back into WPML.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-border">
          <span class="text-xs text-slate-600">No glossary. No profiles. No history.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem-card {
    @apply p-7 flex flex-col rounded-2xl;
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .problem-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.08);
  }

  .icon-wrap {
    @apply w-10 h-10 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }
</style>
